-- South African Central Bank's Mminele Says Inflows Risk Asset Price Bubble
-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 2010-11-19T05:18:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/south-african-central-bank-s-mminele-says-inflows-risk-asset-price-bubble.html
South African Reserve Bank Deputy
Governor Daniel Mminele said “significant” capital inflows
into emerging markets are putting “appreciation pressure” on
currencies, leading to uneven recoveries and risk facilitating
asset price bubbles.  Mminele commented in a speech published on the Pretoria-
based central bank’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  